337
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:25,440
Coincidentally...

338
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,340
Right! What a coincidence!

339
00:22:27,340 --> 00:22:29,780
And I'm even luckier that you're letting me pay in installments, too.

340
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:32,560
I don't have ฿30,000-40,000 to pay you back all at once...
(Approx. $950-1,265 USD)

341
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:36,300
After a while, you're actually a pretty good person, too, Ai'Tin.

342
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:41,940
So am I good enough to hit on you yet?

343
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:47,820
Can.

344
00:22:47,820 --> 00:22:49,980
I don't know.

345
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:53,240
Just tell me yes or no.

346
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,920
But I just don't know.

347
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:59,800
I just know... that I don't get goosebumps when you hit on me.

348
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:03,940
Then I'm going to get serious now.

349
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:07,640
I don't know! I'm sleepy. That's all for now...

350
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:18,620
I'm going to be serious, for real now.

351
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:55,140
Ae?

352
00:23:55,140 --> 00:23:57,180
I'm going to buy stuff at 7 Eleven. Do you want to come with?

353
00:23:57,180 --> 00:23:59,080
I'll go, too.

354
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,520
Hello, Tar.

355
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:14,740
Hello, P'Tum.

356
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:16,100
How have you been?

357
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:19,680
Well, pretty good still. My school just started.

358
00:24:19,740 --> 00:24:20,820
I've been a little bit busy.

359
00:24:20,820 --> 00:24:21,840
And how is it over there?

360
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,260
Pretty good.

361
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:29,180
Lately, I've been thinking about... what songs I should write.

362
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:31,080
Writing songs?

363
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:33,040
Are you writing them to be an artist now?

364
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,940
For the song... How far have you gotten with writing it?

365
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:38,580
I still don't know what genre it should be.

366
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,900
I have no idea.

367
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:45,980
Then I think for now... maybe a love song? It seems to be in now.

368
00:24:45,980 --> 00:24:47,720
A love song?

369
00:24:50,220 --> 00:24:51,500
I don't know.

370
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,420
What are you doing now?

371
00:24:53,420 --> 00:24:55,180
Oh... I just happened to be doing this.

372
00:24:55,180 --> 00:25:01,700
Sitting doing various assignments. Sitting and reading articles and such for a project.

373
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:05,640
And I figured after finishing up in a bit, I was going to take a shower.

374
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,420
How is it over there?

375
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:10,000
Is the climate starting to get colder?

376
00:25:10,860 --> 00:25:12,120
Well, it's Thailand.

377
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:14,360
It's as hot as ever.

378
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:19,260
Either way, if you ever have a chance, want to try visiting me?

379
00:25:19,940 --> 00:25:23,080
By the way, when are you coming back?

380
00:25:25,620 --> 00:25:27,500
I'm still not sure yet.

381
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:31,020
But if I'm free or have a long holiday break,

382
00:25:31,020 --> 00:25:32,940
I'll go back to see you.

383
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:35,500
Tell dad and mom that I miss them, too, all right?

384
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:37,200
If you come back this time,

385
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,120
will I get to try your desserts?

386
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:43,820
I guarantee that you'll definitely get to eat them! Because I've already taken the dessert class this year.

387
00:25:43,820 --> 00:25:47,360
I should be better than before, probably.

388
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,860
It's a holiday break over there, right?

389
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:52,040
Yes.

390
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:54,960
Then I won't bother you anymore.

391
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:58,960
Okay. I'll take a shower and go to bed then.

392
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:00,540
Sweet dreams.

393
00:26:00,540 --> 00:26:03,400
Okay. Then, sweet dreams all right?

394
00:26:12,060 --> 00:26:15,260
Dad, I'm bored.

395
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:19,300
Didn't I tell you to go with your mom?

396
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,840
I don't want to.

397
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,780
Grandma's always nagging.

398
00:26:22,780 --> 00:26:24,460
I don't like it.

399
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:27,220
I like being with Dad more.

400
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:31,040
But you said you were bored.

401
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:34,840
Dad, can you tell me a story?

402
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:37,020
I'm still working.

403
00:26:37,020 --> 00:26:39,760
It's late now. You need to rest.

404
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:42,160
You can't work, Dad.

405
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:43,740
Rest?

406
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:47,060
Then that means that I don't have to tell you a story, right?

407
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:52,020
I don't want that. You have to tell me a story.

408
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:59,180
Well… How about the story...

409
00:27:00,060 --> 00:27:01,860
of two brothers? Sound good?

410
00:27:01,860 --> 00:27:05,780
No, I don't want it. It doesn't sound exciting.

411
00:27:07,020 --> 00:27:11,800
Then...the story of two brothers and one other, a servant?

412
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,840
It doesn't seem very fun.

413
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,240
Once upon a long time ago,

414
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,620
there were two brothers.

415
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:25,800
The older one was a jealous kid

416
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,960
who wanted revenge on everyone.

417
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,540
As for the younger brother, he was a naughty kid.

418
00:27:32,540 --> 00:27:35,140
He was raised very spoiled until he was ruined.

419
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:40,520
But it was the older brother who purposely raised him to be ruined.

420
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:43,940
If he was someone with a bad personality, no one would love him.

421
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:46,920
Until one day...

422
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,480
What right do you have to tell me what to do?

423
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,200
You're just a servant.

424
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:54,120
Whatever I do is my business.

425
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:59,620
Khun Tin... but if you speak like this, it's not nice.
(T/N: Khun is an honorific that basically =Mr./Ms./Mrs.)

426
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:02,060
If Khun Tul heard it, he probably wouldn't like it either.

427
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:04,400
Well, I'm not speaking to P'Tul, am I?

428
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:08,140
I speak like this only to servants like you.

429
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:10,680
You have no right to tell me what I can and can't do.

430
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:12,920
Did you hear me?

431
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:14,820
Yes. I understand that I have no right.

432
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:16,960
Good. Now move over.

433
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,600
Khun Rasa ordered me not to let you go out.

434
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,620
Move over!

435
00:28:22,620 --> 00:28:25,080
I can't, Khun Tin. Please wait for Tul to come back first.

436
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:25,960
Move!

437
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:28,680
I'll make them pay for what they did to Tul.

438
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,140
You really can't do that.

439
00:28:31,140 --> 00:28:33,880
Khun Rasa ordered me to keep you out of trouble.

440
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,980
But they insulted P'Tul.

441
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:38,880
I still can't let you go.

442
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,940
You should follow only Tul's orders,

443
00:28:41,940 --> 00:28:43,540
not my mom's.

444
00:28:43,540 --> 00:28:46,180
I will tell Tul about this.

445
00:28:46,180 --> 00:28:49,960
Sure. If it will make you feel better, then you can go ahead and tell Khun Tul.

446
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:02,600
I didn't mean to!

447
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:12,380
- What happened?
- He... He put himself in front of me.

448
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:14,220
I didn't do anything.

449
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:16,200
Shut up right now, Tin!

450
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:34,840
Only spoiling the younger made the older brother unable to stand it anymore.

451
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:39,040
What happened after that?

452
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:41,760
Did the younger brother get punished?

453
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:42,960
Of course, he was punished.

454
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:44,720
Nong Phu, remember this all right?

455
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:47,240
Don't be like that naughty kid.

456
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,300
I'm a good kid.

457
00:29:49,300 --> 00:29:51,920
I'm a good kid, really.

458
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:55,820
I'm not like the younger brother. He's bad.

459
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,940
That's right.

460
00:29:59,020 --> 00:30:01,760
Bad children need to be punished.

461
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,380
A kid with a bad personality,

462
00:30:03,380 --> 00:30:05,840
no one has a need for them.

463
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:13,360
Why didn't you also tell him

464
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:15,860
just who the one was that taught such bad things to the younger brother?

465
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:19,640
Who made that younger brother have no one around him?

466
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,300
Go ahead and tell him.

467
00:30:22,980 --> 00:30:24,440
Dad.

468
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:27,700
Uncle Tin. Uncle Tin, don't hurt Dad.

469
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,180
Nong Phu, remember this, all right?

470
00:30:40,820 --> 00:30:43,240
Whether you'll be like the older or younger brother,

471
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:48,860
don't be a monster disguised as an angel.

472
00:30:53,020 --> 00:30:54,880
Or don't be a stupid person

473
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,920
who just gets fooled repeatedly.

474
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,240
Do you understand?

475
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,660
Yes...

476
00:31:09,960 --> 00:31:12,880
Dad, Uncle Tin is so scary.

477
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,240
It's okay.

478
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,100
Uncle Tin is probably just tired.

479
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:22,960
Sit here.

480
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,120
Nong Phu, remember this

481
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:32,120
Don't be like those two brothers.

482
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:34,520
Especially the older brother,

483
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:36,960
the one who must pay for his sins.

484
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:43,980
He's paying for his sins still.

485
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,420
Khun Tul,

486
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:14,360
did something happen to you?

487
00:35:09,420 --> 00:35:13,620
[Thanks for the snacks. They were damn delicious!]

488
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:18,520
Hey! Again?

489
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:21,580
I still haven't finished texting yet! Why are you calling?

490
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:30,900
If you listen to what I have to say,

491
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,780
would you believe me?

492
00:35:34,679 --> 00:35:35,520
Of course, I'd believe you.

493
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:36,900
Because you're my friend.

494
00:35:36,900 --> 00:35:39,200
Whatever you say, I'd believe you anyway.

495
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:54,540
I used to think that my older brother

496
00:35:54,540 --> 00:35:57,540
was everything to me.

497
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:02,600
My older brother was everything that I had.

498
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:06,040
No matter what he said,

499
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,740
I'd believe him.

500
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,620
He had told me that

501
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,680
dad and mom didn't love me.

502
00:36:19,660 --> 00:36:22,140
I believed everything.

503
00:36:24,940 --> 00:36:27,860
I believed even the words of his lies,

504
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,940
that he said he would help me

505
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:35,380
when I was being accused of abusing drugs.

506
00:36:35,380 --> 00:36:37,380
Huh? What was that?

507
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:49,380
I grew up to be a spoiled child

508
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:51,640
with a bad personality,

509
00:36:53,980 --> 00:36:56,160
and that bad child

510
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:59,040
had to be sent to study abroad.

511
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:05,200
I partied

512
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,100
and went out.

513
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:13,580
And then I was arrested

514
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:17,180
on charges of using drugs.

515
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:21,660
Even though I didn't even know that it was a drug party.

516
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:28,120
It was all over the news.

517
00:37:28,780 --> 00:37:31,480
I was on the front pages.

518
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:37,200
"A drug-addicted socialite

519
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,540
was arrested abroad."

520
00:37:45,140 --> 00:37:47,820
My older brother said that he would help me.

521
00:37:51,580 --> 00:37:55,300
But the truth was he was the one behind everything.

522
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,380
He hates me.

523
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:01,800
He wants me dead.

524
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:04,240
He wants to take everything from me.

525
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,940
Hates me...

526
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:24,840
Ai'Tin, where are you?

527
00:38:26,740 --> 00:38:27,260
